<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-668-232  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 668 232.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Communications News  August 1989 v26 n8 p22(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Good advice for users; technology gets real at Texpo.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Hirsch, Marina.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The Visionary Network walk-through exhibit at Texpo '89 boastedabout the advantages of Broadband ISDN and offered a preview ofvideo teleconferencing, electronic archiving, medical imaging andhigh-definition television.andP;  Virtual Reality technology from VPLResearch was the exhibit's star.andP;  Reality Built for Two (RB2)combines VPL Eyephones, goggles with a video screen for each eye,and fiber optic gloves to convert hand motions to machine-readablecommands.andP;  The system allows users to move within athree-dimensional computer-generated reality, which can be sharedover a broadband ISDN network.andP;  The complete system for two costs$430,000.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     TexpoTrade showsISDNTelecommunicationsNetworksNew Technique.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>